feat(ui): apply Apple HIG to student dashboard

Completes the student-facing pages (Home, Exam, Result, Dashboard).
Admin panel still uses its own legacy theme (separate concern).

dashboard.html:
- Switched from .dashboard-* legacy markup to .dash-* HIG classes
  (.dashboard-page, .dash-topbar, .dash-container, .dash-profile,
  .dash-section, .dash-section-title, .dash-loading, .dash-footer).
- Removed link to legacy css/pages/dashboard.css (only main.css now).
- Replaced inline `style="display:none"` with `hidden` attribute
  for accessibility — sections show via JS toggling .hidden = false.

dashboard/index.js:
- All `style.display = 'block'/'none'` calls now use the `.hidden`
  attribute (a11y best practice, consistent with rest of app).
- Error fallback uses .dash-section instead of removed .dashboard-empty.
- The stat-card / subject-bar / history-item classes remain as-is —
  these are already wired through public/css/pages/_dashboard.css.

scripts/capture-visuals.mjs:
- Added `captureDashboard()` that mocks /api/dashboard via fetch stub,
  rendering full dashboard with sample profile + stats + 5 subjects
  + 5 history entries. Bypasses auth (mock token + intercepted fetch).
- Now supports CLI args: `node capture-visuals.mjs [pages...]`
  e.g. `node capture-visuals.mjs dashboard home`.

Cleanup:
- Removed legacy public/css/pages/dashboard.css (replaced by _dashboard.css).

Visual verified for both light + dark themes.
